    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
        This function is used to choose which way of implementation to execute. Runs Implementor in two possible ways:
        • 2 arguments: className rootPath - runs implement(Class, Path) with first two arguments
        • 3 arguments: -jar className jarPath - runs implementJar(Class, Path) with second two arguments
        If arguments are incorrect or an error occurs during implementation returns message with information about error
        Parameters:
        args - an arguments

      • generateImplementation

        private static java.lang.StringBuilder generateImplementation​(java.lang.Class<?> token)
        Generates an implementation. Generate full simple class implementation for this interface in following order:
        1. Generates package: generatePackage
        2. Generates declaration: generateDeclaration
        3. Generates Methods: generateMethods
        Parameters:
        token - interface
        Returns:
        Header, Body and Footer of class

      • generateMethods

        private static java.lang.StringBuilder generateMethods​(java.lang.Class<?> token)
        Generates all methods. Generates all public and private methods of interface in following order:
        1. Chooses modifier: PRIVATE or PUBLIC
        2. Generates all of Exception if exists
        3. Generate base return using getDefaultType
        Parameters:
        token - class
        Returns:
        Body, that contains methods

      • getDefaultType

        private static java.lang.String getDefaultType​(java.lang.Class type)
        Returns default type. Take a type and choose one of:
        • FALSE for Boolean
        • EMPTY_STRING for String and Void
        • ZERO for Integer
        • NULL for others
        Parameters:
        type - class
        Returns:
        String of default parameter of any types
